# yabai - Tiling Window Manager

Automatic window tiling for macOS, inspired by bspwm and i3.

## Setup

1. Install: `brew install koekeishiya/formulae/yabai`
2. Start service: `yabai --start-service`
3. Grant accessibility permissions (System Settings → Privacy & Security → Accessibility)

## Configuration

- `yabairc` - Main config (BSP layout, gaps, opacity, rules)
- Integrates with skhd for hotkeys
- Uses borders for visual feedback

## Features in This Config

- BSP (binary space partition) layout
- 8px gaps and padding
- Window opacity (50% inactive, 100% active)
- No animations (fast)
- Borders integration (active window highlight)
- System Settings/Dialogs unmanaged

